<subSubSection id="8AE96506FFEE6817FF4AFA4DCD58F9F5" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C24C368DFFEE6817FF4AFA4DCD6BFA49" blockId="104.[189,636,1445,1472]" box="[189,636,1445,1472]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<heading id="990481E1FFEE6817FF4AFA4DCD6BFA49" bold="true" box="[189,636,1445,1472]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" reason="3">
<emphasis id="F087EA9FFFEE6817FF4AFA4DCD6BFA49" bold="true" box="[189,636,1445,1472]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Character states and colour pattern</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C24C368DFFEE6817FF4AFA3CCD58F9F5" blockId="104.[189,1399,1492,1661]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="05F34D0EFFEE6817FEC2FA3DCD36FA67" authorityName="d’Acoz &amp; Verheye" authorityYear="2017" box="[309,545,1493,1518]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epimeriidae" genus="Epimeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gargantua">
<emphasis id="F087EA9FFFEE6817FEC2FA3DCD36FA67" box="[309,545,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Epimeria gargantua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with a different colour pattern. Background colour of the body: white; all pereionites with two pairs of small red spots disposed transversally; pereionite 1 + coxa 1, pereionite 4 + coxa 4, pereionite 7 + coxa 7 with broad orange red stripe; urosomite 1 and basis of pereiopod 7 orange red; basis of pereiopods 5–6 white; antennae and pereiopods (except basis of pereiopods 5–7) pink; mouthparts purple; eyes red.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8AE96506FFEE6817FF4AF94BCB2AF8BD" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C24C368DFFEE6817FF4AF94BCE41F934" blockId="104.[189,342,1699,1725]" box="[189,342,1699,1725]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
